quran[31]{c,v,t,f}:
  74,43,"They will say: ",footnotes:1:{74:43} See the footnote of {8:39}.
  74,44,""
  74,45,"",footnotes:1:{74:45} See the footnote of {4:5}.
  75,40,"Is not He (Allâh Who does that) Able to give life to the dead? (Yes! He is Able to do all things)."
  77,31,"Neither shady, nor of any use against the fierce flame of the Fire."
  77,32,"Verily, it (Hell) throws sparks (huge) as Al-Qasr (a fort or a huge log of wood),"
  77,33,"As if they were yellow camels or bundles of ropes."
  78,28,"But they belied Our Ayât (proofs, evidence, verses, lessons, signs, revelations, and that which Our Prophet صلى الله عليه وسلم brought) completely."
  78,29,"And all things We have recorded in a Book."
  78,30,"So taste you (the results of your evil actions). No increase shall We give you, except in torment."
  79,22,"Then he turned his back, striving (against Allâh)."
  79,23,"Then he gathered (his people) and cried aloud,"
  79,24,"Saying: "
  80,19,"From Nutfah (male and female semen drops) He created him and then set him in due proportion."
  80,20,"Then He makes the Path easy for him."
  80,21,"Then He causes him to die and puts him in his grave."
  81,16,"And by the planets that move swiftly and hide themselves."
  81,17,"And by the night as it departs."
  81,18,"And by the dawn as it brightens."
  82,10,"But verily, over you (are appointed angels in charge of mankind) to watch you,{1}",footnotes:1:{82:10} Narrated Abu Hurairah رضي الله عنه: The Prophet صلى الله عليه وسلم said: "Angels come (to you) in succession by night and day, and all of them get together at the time of the Fajr and ‘Asr prayers. Then those who have stayed with you overnight, ascend unto Allâh, Who asks them (and He knows the answer better than they): "How have you left My slaves?" They reply, "We left them while they were praying and we came to them while they were praying". The Prophet صلى الله عليه وسلم added: "If anyone of you says Amîn (during the prayer at the end of the recitation of Sûrat Al-Fâtihah), and the angels in heaven say the same, and the two sayings coincide, all his past sins will be forgiven". (Sahih Al-Bukhari, Vol.4, Hadith No.446).
  82,11,"Kirâman (Honourable) Kâtibîn writing down (your deeds),{1}",footnotes:1:{82:11} Whoever intended to do a good deed or a bad deed.
  82,12,"They know all that you do."
  83,7,"Nay! Truly, the Record (writing of the deeds) of the Fujjâr (disbelievers, polytheists, sinners, evil-doers and the wicked) is (preserved) in Sijjîn."
  83,8,"And what will make you know what Sijjîn is?"
  83,9,"A Register inscribed."
  84,4,"And has cast out all that was in it and became empty."
  84,5,"And listens to and obeys its Lord - and it must do so."
  84,6,"O man! Verily, you are returning towards your Lord with your deeds and actions (good or bad), a sure returning, and you will meet (the results of your deeds which you did)."
  85,1,"By the heaven holding the big stars.{1}",footnotes:1:{85:1} (About the) Stars, Abu Qatâdah mentioning Allâh’s Statement:
  85,2,"And by the Promised Day (i.e. the Day of Resurrection)."
  85,3,"And by the Witnessing day (i.e. Friday), and by the Witnessed day [i.e. the day of ‘Arafât (Hajj) the ninth of Dhul-Hijjah];"